Package a prosody 0.10.0 RPM for use on CentOS 7
0- vagrant up

0. Install dependencies
sudo yum install rpmdevtools
sudo yum install lua-devel openssl-devel libidn-devel
sudo yum install gcc

0.b. rpmdev-setuptree


1. Download prosody-0.10.0.tar.gz
2. Move sources to ~/rpmbuild/SOURCES
3. Build RPM:
	rpmbuild -bb prosody.spec 

! Build an RPM - Yeah.
